          "stepNumber": 1,
          "explanation": "Use the formula $^nP_r = n \\times (n-1) \\times \\cdots \\times (n-r+1)$. Here $n=50$, $r=48$, so we need 48 factors starting from 50.",
          "formula": "nPr formula",
          "formulaExpression": "^nP_r = \\frac{n!}{(n-r)!}",
          "calculation": "$^{50}P_{48} = \\frac{50!}{(50-48)!} = \\frac{50!}{2!} = 50 \\times 49 = 2450$",
          "result": "2450"
        },
        {
          "stepNumber": 2,
          "explanation": "Alternatively, $^{50}P_{48} = 50 \\times 49 = 2450$",
          "formula": null,
          "formulaExpression": "50 \\times 49",
          "calculation": "50 × 49 = 2450",
          "result": "2450"
        }
      ],
      "shortcut": "$^nP_{n-2} = n(n-1)$",
      "commonMistake": "Confusing $^nP_r$ with $^nC_r$; not simplifying the factorial correctly.",
      "timeToSolve": "30 seconds"
    },
    "modelName": "Evaluate nPr",
